<div id="main">
  <h1 id="title">Mahatma Gandhi</h1>
  <div>The Father of Indian Nation</div>
  <div id="img-div">
    <img id="image" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*omubHP3AmKqSsJQO6OZ5bg.jpeg" alt ="Mahatma Gandhi">
    <div id="img-caption">
       Indian activist who was the leader of the Indian independence movement against British rule
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="tribute-info">
    <ul>
      <h3 id="headline">Here's a time line of Mahatma Gandhi:</h3>
      <li><strong>1869</strong> - Born in Porbandar,Gujarat</li>
      <li><strong>1887</strong> - 18-year-old Gandhi graduated from high school in Ahmedabad</li>
      <li><strong>1893</strong> - He spent 21 years in South Africa, where he developed his political views, ethics and politics.</li>
      <li><strong>1903</strong> - When British Declared war against Zulu Kingdom he encouraged the Indian volunteers to help as an ambulance unit.</li>
      <li><strong>1910</strong> - Gandhi established an idealistic community called 'Tolstoy Farm' near Johannesburg, where he nurtured his policy of peaceful resistance.</li>
      <li><strong>1942</strong> - Speech about Quit India Movement in Mumbai.</li>
      <li><strong>1948</strong> - dies at the age of 79.</li>
    </ul>
    <blockquote>
      <p>Gandhi demanded fair treatment for the untouchables, Indiaâ€™s lowest caste, and he underwent several fasts to support the cause. He called the untouchables harijans, which means "children of God."</p>
    </blockquote>
